***REMOVED*** =============================================================================
***REMOVED*** Residency Scheduler - Environment Configuration
***REMOVED*** =============================================================================
***REMOVED*** Copy this file to .env and fill in your values
***REMOVED*** NEVER commit .env to version control
***REMOVED*** =============================================================================

***REMOVED*** -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
***REMOVED*** Database Configuration
***REMOVED*** -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
***REMOVED*** PostgreSQL password for the scheduler user
***REMOVED*** Use a strong, unique password in production
DB_PASSWORD=your_secure_database_password_here

***REMOVED*** -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
***REMOVED*** Security Configuration
***REMOVED*** -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
***REMOVED*** Secret key for JWT token signing
***REMOVED*** Generate with: python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_urlsafe(64))"
***REMOVED*** CRITICAL: Use a unique, random value in production
SECRET_KEY=your_secret_key_here_generate_a_random_64_char_string

***REMOVED*** Webhook secret for validating incoming webhook requests
***REMOVED*** Generate with: python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_urlsafe(64))"
***REMOVED*** CRITICAL: Use a unique, random value in production (minimum 32 characters)
WEBHOOK_SECRET=your_webhook_secret_here_generate_a_random_64_char_string

***REMOVED*** Redis password for authentication
***REMOVED*** Generate with: python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_urlsafe(32))"
***REMOVED*** For development: defaults to 'dev_only_password' if not set
***REMOVED*** For production: MUST be set to a strong random value
REDIS_PASSWORD=your_redis_password_here_generate_a_random_string

***REMOVED*** -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
***REMOVED*** Application Configuration
***REMOVED*** -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
***REMOVED*** Debug mode - set to false in production
***REMOVED*** Enables detailed error messages and hot reload in development
DEBUG=true

***REMOVED*** -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
***REMOVED*** gRPC Configuration (optional)
***REMOVED*** -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
***REMOVED*** Port for gRPC server (if enabled)
***REMOVED*** Default: 50051 (standard gRPC port)
GRPC_PORT=50051

***REMOVED*** Maximum number of concurrent gRPC workers
***REMOVED*** Increase for high-traffic deployments
***REMOVED*** Default: 10
GRPC_MAX_WORKERS=10

***REMOVED*** Enable TLS/SSL for gRPC connections
***REMOVED*** Production: true (requires valid certificates)
***REMOVED*** Development: false (unencrypted connections)
GRPC_ENABLE_TLS=false

***REMOVED*** Path to TLS certificate file (required if GRPC_ENABLE_TLS=true)
***REMOVED*** Example: /etc/ssl/certs/grpc-server.pem
***REMOVED*** GRPC_TLS_CERT_PATH=/path/to/cert.pem

***REMOVED*** Path to TLS private key file (required if GRPC_ENABLE_TLS=true)
***REMOVED*** Example: /etc/ssl/private/grpc-server-key.pem
***REMOVED*** GRPC_TLS_KEY_PATH=/path/to/key.pem

***REMOVED*** -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
***REMOVED*** Error Reporting Configuration (optional)
***REMOVED*** -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
***REMOVED*** Sentry DSN for error tracking and monitoring
***REMOVED*** Sign up at https://sentry.io/ to get your DSN
***REMOVED*** Leave empty to disable Sentry error reporting
***REMOVED*** Format: https://<key>@sentry.io/<project_id>
***REMOVED*** SENTRY_DSN=https://examplePublicKey@o0.ingest.sentry.io/0

***REMOVED*** -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
***REMOVED*** Single Sign-On (SSO) Configuration (optional)
***REMOVED*** -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
***REMOVED*** Enable SSO authentication (requires additional configuration)
***REMOVED*** Default: false (use local authentication)
***REMOVED*** SSO_ENABLED=false

***REMOVED*** Enable SAML 2.0 authentication
***REMOVED*** Requires SSO_ENABLED=true and SAML identity provider setup
***REMOVED*** SSO_SAML_ENABLED=false

***REMOVED*** Enable OAuth2/OIDC authentication
***REMOVED*** Requires SSO_ENABLED=true and OAuth provider configuration
***REMOVED*** Examples: Azure AD, Okta, Google Workspace
***REMOVED*** SSO_OAUTH2_ENABLED=false

***REMOVED*** -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
***REMOVED*** Notification Email Configuration (optional)
***REMOVED*** -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
***REMOVED*** Email addresses for compliance violation notifications
***REMOVED*** Format: comma-separated list of email addresses
***REMOVED*** Example: compliance@hospital.mil,quality@hospital.mil
***REMOVED*** COMPLIANCE_STAKEHOLDER_EMAILS=compliance@example.com

***REMOVED*** Email addresses for executive reports and critical alerts
***REMOVED*** Format: comma-separated list of email addresses
***REMOVED*** Example: cmo@hospital.mil,chief-of-staff@hospital.mil
***REMOVED*** EXECUTIVE_STAKEHOLDER_EMAILS=exec@example.com

***REMOVED*** -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
***REMOVED*** CORS Configuration
***REMOVED*** -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
***REMOVED*** Allowed origins for cross-origin requests
***REMOVED*** In production, set to your actual frontend domain
***REMOVED*** Format: JSON array of strings
CORS_ORIGINS=["http://localhost:3000"]

***REMOVED*** -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
***REMOVED*** Frontend Configuration
***REMOVED*** -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
***REMOVED*** Backend API URL that the frontend will use
***REMOVED*** In production, use your actual backend domain/IP
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:8000

***REMOVED*** -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
***REMOVED*** MCP Server Configuration
***REMOVED*** -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
***REMOVED*** Log level for MCP server (DEBUG, INFO, WARNING, ERROR)
***REMOVED*** DEBUG shows all tool invocations and API calls
MCP_LOG_LEVEL=INFO

***REMOVED*** =============================================================================
***REMOVED*** OpenTelemetry / Distributed Tracing Configuration
***REMOVED*** =============================================================================
***REMOVED*** Provides distributed tracing across backend services (API, workers, scheduler)
***REMOVED*** Useful for debugging latency issues, tracking request flows, and monitoring dependencies
***REMOVED*** Default: TELEMETRY_ENABLED=false (disabled for development to avoid performance impact)
***REMOVED***
***REMOVED*** PRODUCTION SETUP:
***REMOVED*** 1. Enable tracing: TELEMETRY_ENABLED=true
***REMOVED*** 2. Set backend endpoint (where traces are exported):
***REMOVED***    - Jaeger all-in-one: http://jaeger:16686 (or your host:port)
***REMOVED***    - OpenTelemetry Collector: http://otel-collector:4317 (gRPC) or :4318 (HTTP)
***REMOVED***    - Zipkin: http://zipkin:9411
***REMOVED*** 3. Set TELEMETRY_EXPORTER_INSECURE=false in production (use TLS)
***REMOVED*** 4. Add authentication headers if your backend requires it

***REMOVED*** Enable distributed tracing globally
***REMOVED*** Default: false (disabled for development)
***REMOVED*** Set to true in production to enable
TELEMETRY_ENABLED=false

***REMOVED*** Service identification (used in trace metadata)
***REMOVED*** This appears in your tracing backend (e.g., Jaeger service list)
TELEMETRY_SERVICE_NAME=residency-scheduler

***REMOVED*** Deployment environment tag
***REMOVED*** Values: development, staging, production
***REMOVED*** Used to filter and label traces by environment
TELEMETRY_ENVIRONMENT=development

***REMOVED*** Sampling configuration (0.0 to 1.0, where 1.0 = 100% sampling)
***REMOVED*** 1.0 = trace every request (high data volume, useful for debugging)
***REMOVED*** 0.1 = trace 10% of requests (better for high-traffic production)
***REMOVED*** 0.01 = trace 1% of requests (minimal overhead, sparse data)
TELEMETRY_SAMPLING_RATE=1.0

***REMOVED*** Console debug output (useful for local development)
***REMOVED*** When enabled, prints spans to console in addition to backend exporter
***REMOVED*** Set to false in production to reduce log noise
TELEMETRY_CONSOLE_EXPORT=false

***REMOVED*** Exporter backend type
***REMOVED*** Supported types:
***REMOVED***   - otlp_grpc (default): OpenTelemetry Protocol via gRPC (port 4317)
***REMOVED***   - otlp_http: OpenTelemetry Protocol via HTTP (port 4318)
***REMOVED***   - jaeger: Jaeger all-in-one exporter (port 6831)
***REMOVED***   - zipkin: Zipkin JSON exporter (port 9411)
TELEMETRY_EXPORTER_TYPE=otlp_grpc

***REMOVED*** Exporter endpoint URL
***REMOVED*** OTLP gRPC: http://localhost:4317 or https://otel.mycompany.com:4317
***REMOVED*** OTLP HTTP: http://localhost:4318 or https://otel.mycompany.com:4318
***REMOVED*** Jaeger: http://localhost:6831
***REMOVED*** Zipkin: http://localhost:9411/api/v2/spans
***REMOVED***
***REMOVED*** Docker Compose setup:
***REMOVED***   http://otel-collector:4317 (or your service name)
***REMOVED*** Kubernetes setup:
***REMOVED***   http://otel-collector.monitoring:4317
TELEMETRY_EXPORTER_ENDPOINT=http://localhost:4317

***REMOVED*** Use insecure connection (no TLS)
***REMOVED*** Development: true (most OTEL collectors listen on insecure by default)
***REMOVED*** Production: false (use TLS for security)
TELEMETRY_EXPORTER_INSECURE=true

***REMOVED*** Optional: Authentication headers for exporter (JSON format)
***REMOVED*** Example: {"Authorization": "Bearer YOUR_API_KEY"}
***REMOVED*** Used for:
***REMOVED***   - Datadog: {"DD-API-KEY": "your-api-key"}
***REMOVED***   - New Relic: {"api-key": "your-api-key"}
***REMOVED***   - Custom backends with auth
***REMOVED*** Uncomment and set if your backend requires authentication
***REMOVED*** TELEMETRY_EXPORTER_HEADERS={"Authorization": "Bearer token"}

***REMOVED*** =============================================================================
***REMOVED*** Instrumentation Toggles
***REMOVED*** =============================================================================
***REMOVED*** Controls which components emit traces
***REMOVED*** Disabling reduces overhead but loses visibility into those systems

***REMOVED*** Enable SQLAlchemy database query tracing
***REMOVED*** Traces all SQL queries, execution times, and errors
***REMOVED*** Default: true (recommended to keep enabled for debugging slow queries)
TELEMETRY_TRACE_SQLALCHEMY=true

***REMOVED*** Enable Redis cache operation tracing
***REMOVED*** Traces cache hits/misses, operations, and latency
***REMOVED*** Default: true (useful for debugging cache performance)
TELEMETRY_TRACE_REDIS=true

***REMOVED*** Enable HTTP client tracing (external API calls)
***REMOVED*** Traces outgoing HTTP requests via requests and httpx libraries
***REMOVED*** Default: true (useful for debugging external service latency)
TELEMETRY_TRACE_HTTP=true

***REMOVED*** -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
***REMOVED*** LLM Router Configuration
***REMOVED*** -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
***REMOVED*** Default LLM provider (ollama, anthropic)
***REMOVED*** ollama = local Docker container, anthropic = cloud API
LLM_DEFAULT_PROVIDER=ollama

***REMOVED*** Enable fallback to other providers on failure
LLM_ENABLE_FALLBACK=true

***REMOVED*** Airgap mode - disable all cloud providers (local only)
***REMOVED*** Set to true for offline/secure deployments
LLM_AIRGAP_MODE=false

***REMOVED*** Ollama configuration (local LLM)
OLLAMA_URL=http://ollama:11434
OLLAMA_DEFAULT_MODEL=llama3.2
OLLAMA_FAST_MODEL=llama3.2
OLLAMA_TOOL_MODEL=mistral
OLLAMA_TIMEOUT=60.0

***REMOVED*** Anthropic API configuration (cloud LLM)
***REMOVED*** Leave empty for airgap mode or local-only operation
***REMOVED*** Get API key from: https://console.anthropic.com/
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
ANTHROPIC_DEFAULT_MODEL=claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022

***REMOVED*** -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
***REMOVED*** Optional: PostgreSQL Direct Connection (for local development)
***REMOVED*** -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
***REMOVED*** Full database URL (usually constructed automatically in docker-compose)
***REMOVED*** DATABASE_URL=postgresql://scheduler:your_password@localhost:5432/residency_scheduler
